name: Seminar on DevOps
description: DevOps is a culture which promotes collaboration between Development and Operations Team to deploy code to production faster in an automated & repeatable way. The word DevOps is a combination of two words development and operations. DevOps helps to increases an organization's speed to deliver applications and services. It allows organizations to serve their customers better and compete more strongly in the market. In simple words, DevOps can be defined as an alignment of development and IT operations with better communication and collaboration.

name: Workshop on IOT
description: The Internet of Things (IoT) is a system of interrelated computing devices, mechanical and digital machines, objects, animals or people that are provided with unique identifiers (UIDs) and the ability to transfer data over a network without requiring human-to-human or human-to-computer interaction. The definition of the Internet of Things has evolved due to the convergence of multiple technologies, real-time analytics, machine learning, commodity sensors, and embedded systems. Traditional fields of embedded systems, wireless sensor networks, control systems, automation (including home and building automation), and others all contribute to enabling the Internet of Things. In the consumer market, IoT technology is most synonymous with products pertaining to the concept of the "smart home", covering devices and appliances (such as lighting fixtures, thermostats, home security systems and cameras, and other home appliances) that support one or more common ecosystems, and can be controlled via devices associated with that ecosystem, such as smartphones and smart speakers

name: Seminar on Online Courses
description: EDC has been working to improve teaching and learning in higher education using a mix of modern information and communication technologies. We specialize in developing curriculum based online content for various technical engineering courses. We have the expertise to develop Shareable Content  Object Reference Model (SCORM) compliant courseware and have worked on several learning delivery models – distance learning, blended learning, Instructor-led-and-managed learning environments. EDC aims at developing content that is learner-centric and distinct from the traditional teacher-centric approach. At EDC we have access to a large pool of Subject Matter Experts (SMEs) for various engineering and technical domains, and expert teams to consult, design, develop and support learning content initiatives for higher education. Our Instructional Design team can create comprehensive, interactive online training content that is suited to the varied learning styles of students.
